fr.enstb.xmlcode
Class ModelProperty

java.lang.Object
  fr.enstb.xmlcode.ModelProperty

public class ModelProperty
extends java.lang.Object

ModelProperty is internally used in XMLMapping

You never need to used it directly, this class maps <property> tags in model file.

Author:
Sylvain Guerin
See Also:
XMLMapping

Constructor Detail

ModelProperty

public ModelProperty(ModelEntity aModelEntity,
                     java.lang.String aName,
                     java.lang.String someXMLTags,
                     java.lang.String aContainsTag,
                     java.lang.String aKeyToUse,
                     int aPropertyType,
                     boolean isAttributeFlag,
                     boolean isTextFlag)
              throws InvalidModelException
Creates a new ModelEntity instance
This constructor should be called for dynamically XMLMapping building purposes.
Use ModelEntity.registerNewModelProperty(ModelProperty) to register this new ModelProperty object in an ModelEntity instance.

Parameters:
aModelEntity - a ModelEntity value
aPropertyType - a int value, which could be:
  • SINGLE_PROPERTY_TYPE: this property matches a single object or primitive
  • ARRAY_PROPERTY_TYPE: this property matches a array of objects or primitives
  • VECTOR_PROPERTY_TYPE: this property matches a list of objects stored in a Vector or a sub-class of Vector.
  • HASHTABLE_PROPERTY_TYPE: this property matches a list of objects stored in a Hashtable or a sub-class of Hashtable.
  • PROPERTIES_PROPERTY_TYPE: this property matches a dynamic list of objects stored in a Hashtable or a sub-class of Hashtable where key is a String obtained and parsed from/as XML element name: therefore, there is no need to implement model for contained data
Throws:
InvalidModelException - if an error occurs
